The performance degradation of the PV cells should be ascribed to the impact-induced damages. Therefore, it is crucial to characterize the mechanical damages due to particles’ impact on the PV cells to further reveal the mechanisms of performance degradation. The damage behavior of the PV cells in such an impact environment can be classified into three modes. The first damage mode, denoted by Mode I, is the rupture of the conducting grid lines by impact loadings as depicted by the green arrows in Fig. 6. The critical stress (σI\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
